The paper presents a new deep architecture for probabilistic clustering, which combines deep learning and self-organizing maps. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on clustering and representation learning, it is less likely to belong to sub-categories such as computer architecture (cs.AR) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
